Preheat your #grill{} to high. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the @macaroni{180%g}.

When boiling, add the pasta to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Lay in the @British streaky bacon{8} rashers and fry until crispy and brown, ~{3-4%minutes} on each side (cook in batches if necessary).

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Once cooked, transfer to a #plate{} lined with kitchen paper and keep the bacon fat in the pan.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{90%g}.

Pop the frying pan back on medium-high heat. Melt in the @butter{20%g}, then stir in the @plain flour{1.5%tbsp}. Cook until it forms a paste, ~{1-2%minutes} - you've made a roux!

Gradually stir in the @water{250%ml} for the sauce, @creme fraiche{150%g} and @chicken stock paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, stir and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, chop the crispy bacon into small pieces.

Once thickened, remove the sauce from the heat and stir in the grated Cheddar, cooked macaroni and half the chopped bacon. Season with salt and pepper if needed.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

Pop the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g}, @Parmigiano Reggiano{20%g}(grated) and remaining chopped bacon into a small #bowl{}. Season with lots of @ground black pepper{}, then mix to combine.

Transfer the pasta to an #ovenproof dish{} and top with the breadcrumb mixture.

Grill until the breadcrumbs are golden and the cheese has melted, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}.

In a medium bowl, mix together the @honey{15%g}, @wholegrain mustard{17%g} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with salt and pepper, then add the tomatoes to the bowl.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it into a bowl of hot water for ~{1%minute}.

Just before serving, add the @wild rocket{40%g} and toss to coat.

Serve up your ultimate bacon mac & cheese on plates with the honey mustard dressed salad alongside. Enjoy!